7:        mode: \"non-main\", // \r\ngroups/channels are non-main -> sandboxed\r\nC:\\Users\\16343\\AppData\\Local\\Programs\\ClawX\\resources\\openclaw\\docs\\channels\\groups.md:84:    sandbox: {\r\nC:\\Users\\16343\\AppData\\Local\\Programs\\ClawX\\resources\\openclaw\\docs\\channels\\groups.md:95:Want ��groups can only see fol\r\nder X�� instead of ��no host access��? Keep `workspaceAccess: \"none\"` and mount only allowlisted paths into the sandbox:\r\nC:\\Users\\16343\\AppData\\Local\\Programs\\ClawX\\resources\\openclaw\\docs\\channels\\groups.md:101:      sandbox: {\r\nC:\\Users\\16343\\AppData\\Local\\Programs\\ClawX\\resources\\openclaw\\docs\\channels\\groups.md:119:- Configuration keys and def\r\naults: [Gateway configuration](/gateway/configuration#agentsdefaultssandbox)\r\nC:\\Users\\16343\\AppData\\Local\\Programs\\ClawX\\resources\\openclaw\\docs\\channels\\groups.md:120:- Debugging why a tool is bl\r\nocked: [Sandbox vs Tool Policy vs Elevated](/gateway/sandbox-vs-tool-policy-vs-elevated)\r\nC:\\Users\\16343\\AppData\\Local\\Programs\\ClawX\\resources\\openclaw\\docs\\channels\\groups.md:121:- Bind mounts details: [Sand\r\nboxing](/gateway/sandboxing#custom-bind-mounts)\r\nC:\\Users\\16343\\AppData\\Local\\Programs\\ClawX\\resources\\openclaw\\docs\\cli\\docs.md:14:openclaw docs sandbox allowHostContr\r\nol\r\nC:\\Users\\16343\\AppData\\Local\\Programs\\ClawX\\resources\\openclaw\\docs\\cli\\doctor.md:33:- If sandbox mode is enabled but D\r\nocker is unavailable, doctor reports a high-signal warning with remediation (`install Docker` or `openclaw config set a\r\ngents.defaults.sandbox.mode off`).\r\nC:\\Users\\16343\\AppData\\Local\\Programs\\ClawX\\resources\\openclaw\\docs\\cli\\index.md:43:- [`sandbox`](/cli/sandbox)","cwd":"C:\\Users\\16343\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773652397898}}
